##Quanzhou Hotel collapse tracking: Before the collapse occurred in the construction and column deformation, the hotel was fined several times

Function introduction, here is "China News weekly" the head of the weekly gentleman, the influence has the influence you. Come with me to break through the fog, to find the truth, to watch the Times.

Why have you condemned this house

And the interior of the building is still under renovation

As a quarantine observation point?

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
On the night of March 7,9 people escaped from the building where the Xinjia hotel is located in Quanzhou's Licheng district and 71 people were trapped. As of 1600 hours on 8 March, 48 people had been rescued, 10 of whom had died, and the remaining 38 had been sent to four designated hospitals for treatment. As of press time, another 23 people were still being searched. The building's owner, Yang Jinqiang, is under Public Security Bureau control.

Quanzhou Emergency Rescue Leading Group held two briefings on March 8, reported the situation. According to the relevant departments, after the outbreak of NCP, Xinjia hotel was used as a centralized medical observation point to observe people from key epidemic areas or those with relevant travel history.

Su Yanhui, deputy head of the rescue team and acting head of the Licheng district government, said at a press conference on the afternoon of March 8 that 58 people were inside the building when the Xinjia hotel collapsed, among them, 12 accompanied children, 7 returned home, 37 migrant workers, 2 family visits. All personnel had been tested for nucleic acid after entering the fixed observation point and the results were all negative. In addition, the hotel also has management, service and other 16 people, another rental in the building of the traffic personnel 6 people.

The injured were admitted to the First Hospital of Quanzhou, the Second Affiliated Hospital of Fujian Medical University, the 910th Hospital of the Joint Logistics Support Force, and the Quanzhou Hospital of traditional Chinese medicine. The staff of the Administrative Office of the 910th Hospital of the Joint Logistics Support Force told China News Week that the six injured people they had received were currently in critical condition, as well as in mild condition. As for which injured people were sent to which hospital, it was arranged by the Health Commission of Quanzhou City. A staff member on duty at Quanzhou Hospital of traditional Chinese Medicine said in response to China Newsweek that the 14 people they received were all slightly injured.

On the morning of March 8, four national experts, including neurosurgery, thoracic surgery, bone microsurgery and critical care medicine from the first hospital affiliated to the National Sun Yat-sen University, arrived in Quanzhou to guide the rescue. The hospital carries on each injured person the blood phase, the imaging study and so on medical examination, implements to each injured person "one room one team" as well as the necessary psychological dredge, the injured person's condition is stable.

At present, the scene has 15 monitoring-type ambulances on standby, and with 20 pre-hospital emergency personnel to assist rescue. The pre-hospital first aid personnel refers to the medical staff who give first aid to the critically ill patients outside the hospital. Another urban professional team responsible for on-site prevention and control work.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
According to the relevant departments, the collapsed building was built in 2013, covering about 5 acres, the main 7-storey, each floor 1000 square meters, 22 meters high, for the Steel Structure Building. In 2018, it was converted into Xin Jia Hotel and opened in June of that year. The hotel has 66 rooms in total.

The building was under renovation before the incident. A few minutes before the collapse, a shop received a phone call from the building construction staff, said the operation, the first floor of a column deformation. Zhang Yi, the director of the Licheng District Housing Bureau of Quanzhou City, told the media after the event that there were six on the first floor of the building, two of which were originally supermarkets. Before the Spring Festival this year, the owners of the houses took back the supermarket rented on the first floor and redecorated it. But collapses the reason is the decoration to cause or the building body own structure question, also needs to further discriminate.

According to public records, the hotel had been punished several times before: in November 2018, the Licheng branch of the Quanzhou Public Security Bureau ordered it to rectify and fined 3,000 yuan for failing to register as required. In December 2019, the same administrative penalty was imposed for the same problem. In addition, in July 2019, he was also listed in the business exception list of the Licheng branch of the Quanzhou Administration for Industry and Commerce for failing to submit annual reports in accordance with the "measures on annual reports of individual industrial and commercial households" . In August 2019, its premises underwent a change from the sixth floor of the building to the first floor lobby and four to six floors.

Why is this repeatedly fined and the interior of the building is still under renovation of the hotel as a quarantine observation point? China News weekly contacted the Center for Disease Control and Prevention in Licheng district of Quanzhou, and an office worker responded that this was the arrangement made by the Licheng District Health Bureau. But a staff member from the Licheng district health bureau told China News weekly that it was carried out according to documents from a higher level, and it was not clear why the site was chosen. On the afternoon of March 8, China Newsweek repeatedly called the office of the Quanzhou Municipal Health Commission, but no one answered the phone.

The Xin Jia hotel occupied the fourth, fifth and sixth floors of the collapsed building, which had a foot bath called the Qin Yue Mansion and a restaurant called the bourgeois life bar on the third floor, according to China News Week. Other commercial tenants in the building include Fujian Dingxin Renewable Resources Recycling Co. , Ltd. and Quanzhou Quandebao Auto Sales Co. , Ltd. .

On the afternoon of March 8, China News weekly contacted the head of Quandebao Automobile Sales Co. , Ltd. in Quanzhou, who said he rented a Half-floor storefront from his landlord, Yang Jinqiang, for 40,000 yuan a month in 2013, is One of the first businesses to operate in the building. They're the only other car repair company in the building that rents the rest of the ground floor.

Until 2016, the landlord, Yang Jinqiang, had not started to attract investors, the head of Quandebao Automobile Sales Co. , told China News Weekly. Previously, the entire building had only steel frames, with a direct view from the second floor to the bottom of the seventh floor. At that time, Quandebao Automobile Sales Co. , Ltd. will be the seventh floor as the company's staff quarters. The first floor had no solid walls, just glass doors and windows, the columns are actually steel pipe wrapped with wood.

In early 2017, Yang began renovating the Xinjia Hotel, pouring concrete on three to six floors. During the renovation, the glass on the first floor kept cracking, and the tenants failed to respond to Yang and eventually moved out of the building at the end of the year.

According to relevant industrial and commercial information, Yang Jinqiang registered the hotel in 2018. Yang Jinqiang, 65, is a native of Quanzhou. In addition to the hotel, it is also owned by Quanzhou Xinxing Electrical and Mechanical Trading Co. , Ltd. , a legal person registered in 2006 with a registered capital of 3.3 million yuan.
